sdb - stardict browser

use a good dict like
https://github.com/reader-dict/monolingual
dont forget to gunzip .dict.dz to .dict

unlike sdcv, sdb support space in searched word, ie
'think piece' in sdcv will be searched as think and piece even being quoted in shell
that's a BUG. sdb dont do that. you can search the single word 'think piece'.

Do not handle dictzip, you should gunzip .dict.dz to .dict
Do not handle regexp, html
Do not support dict larger than 4GiB
Do not support image, audio or multiple text sametypesequence
Segfault when a lot -ddict supplied, change dflag = bufoff if need
	because i dont need all these
	also im a unskilled programmer and have no enengy to do some stuff.
	(gumbo-parser is fine to work with thou)

supported:

- .syn
- .off: .idx, .syn offset cache
- latin1 accent fold, unicode case fold, ascii case fuzzy match
- read pattern from stdin (useless, because of not handling html

# .syn 's optimization

format of single item
.idx <=255 word| \0| 4 .dict offset| 4 .dict word size
.syn <=255 word| \0| 4 nth word in .idx

converting the "nth word" into offset,size located at corresponding .idx item
is hard to optimize.

do preconverting and writing to .syo or
do like .off but instead of 1 per 64 offset also writing all of them to .ful
and some other plans are abandoned

# .off spec

n*4 offset to .idx, .syn word start
in machine endian

while n = 2+(wordcount-1)/Pagesize, 2 for 0 and offset of last word
Pagesize = 64

# .oft spec revealed by sdcv's source code

30 "StarDict's Cache, Version: 0.2"| 4 0x51a4d1c1| n*4 offset to word start
in machine endian (0x51a4d1c1 is too)

while n = 2+(wordcount-1)/ENTR_PER_PAGE, 2 for 0 and end byte.
ENTR_PER_PAGE = 32

i dont feel happy about its not including last word's offset but calcing runtime.

